  <title>WebKit2.Settings.enable_site_specific_quirks</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
Settings.enable_site_specific_quirks: Boolean (Read / Write / Construct)
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Whether to turn on site-specific quirks. Turning this on will
tell WebKit to use some site-specific workarounds for
better web compatibility. For example, older versions of
MediaWiki will incorrectly send to WebKit a css file with KHTML
workarounds. By turning on site-specific quirks, WebKit will
special-case this and other cases to make some specific sites work.</p>

